## Tech stack standards

### Next.js (App Router, v16+)

- **Dynamic routes** — Route `params` (and `searchParams` when used) are **`Promise<{ ... }>`**. Always **`await params`** in `generateMetadata` and the page component. Sync access will break at runtime (e.g. 404 on `/projects/[slug]`).
- **Metadata** — Use `metadata` / `generateMetadata`; keep titles consistent with the template in root **`layout.tsx`** (`%s · Aaryan Suri`). Use **`getSiteUrl()`** from `@/lib/site` for absolute URLs, not hard-coded production URLs in multiple places.
- **Static generation** — Export **`generateStaticParams`** when all slugs are known from data (e.g. projects from `@/data/projects`).
- **Navigation** — Prefer **`next/link`** for internal routes; **`notFound()`** when a slug doesn’t match data.
- **Images** — **`next/image`** for bundled/optimized images; **`priority`** only for above-the-fold hero images.

### React 19

- Avoid unnecessary client boundaries; **push `"use client"` down** to the smallest subtree (e.g. `Navbar`, `ThemeToggle`, `MagneticHover`).

### Tailwind CSS v4

- Prefer **semantic classes** defined in **`globals.css`** (`.surface-card`, `.section-rule`, `.btn-outline`, `.link-muted`, `.text-gradient`, `.mono`) for consistency.
- Theme via **CSS variables** (e.g. `text-[color:var(--text-secondary)]`, `border-[color:var(--border)]`) so light/dark (`html[data-theme="light"]`) stays coherent.
- Use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) as already used in layouts; **mobile-first** spacing.

### Framer Motion

- Use **`useReducedMotion()`** where animation affects layout or motion-heavy UI (see **`Navbar`**, **`FocusAreasMarquee`** pattern).
- Keep motion subtle; don’t block content or core CTAs on animation.

### Lucide React

- Icon set version may omit some named icons; **`ExternalLink`** and text fallbacks are acceptable when a brand icon isn’t available.

